2001 debut album from the French singer. Produced by her singing/songwriting brother Benjamin Biolay (who has also written for Henri Salvador), Salle Des Pas Perdus is a confident and often beautiful collection of French Pop. On this release, Coralie wears her influences on her sleeve and sounds like a modern day version of Jane Birkin and Francois Hardy, yet her own personality certainly shines through.
